headline: Royal Caribbean Cruises (NYSE:RCL) Announces US$1B Share Buyback as Stocks Dip 13%
summary: Royal Caribbean Cruises (NYSE:RCL) announced a quarterly dividend of $0.75 per share and a $1 billion share repurchase program, but its stock price fell 13% over the past week. These announcements, typically seen as positive, seemed insufficient to counter broader market trends, as the S&P 500 dropped 3% and the Nasdaq 4% amid economic uncertainties and potential impacts of government policies. The market's overall decline suggests that investor sentiment remains cautious, possibly...
